Red Pikmin have a sharp, nose-like spine on their face—and they're immune to fire! They're trusty allies you can rely on in any situation.
Blue Pikmin have special gills that let them breathe underwater. Unsurprisingly, they love the water and are excellent swimmers.
Yellow Pikmin have ear-like membranes on the sides of their heads, and they love electricity so much you can sometimes hear them buzzing.
Purple Pikmin are extra large, and they have little hair-like feelers on their heads. They're super strong—but they're also super slow.
White Pikmin have big red eyes compared to their small, nimble bodies. Don't let their size fool you, though; they're poisonous!
Rock Pikmin are as tough as they come. They can break any crystal or glass with ease.
Winged Pikmin have large eyes, a striped belly, and most importantly, wings! They can fly from place to place quickly, but they're not very strong.

In this world, there are small creatures that look a little like animals and a little like plants. We call them Pikmin.
Pikmin are invisible to the human eye, but can be seen through your smartphone.
